'''Hilter''' is a municipality in the [[OsnabrÃ¼ck (district)|district OsnabrÃ¼ck]], [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It is located in the hills of the [[Teutoburg Forest]].
As of 2002 it has a population of 10,179, and covers an area of 52.61&nbsp;kmÂ². Highest elevation is the Hohnangel with 262 m above sea level.
==History== The municipality was united on July 14, 1972, by merging the municipalities Borgloh, Hankenberge and Hilter. Already in 1977 the municipalities Allendorf, Borgloh-Wellendorf, Ebbendorf, Eppendorf and UphÃ¶fen were joined into the ''Einheitsgemeinde'' Borgloh.
==Industry== {{dx|[[File:HilterTWWalterRauLebensmittelwerke.jpg|thumb|150px|The margarine factory]]}} Hilter was well known for the "Hilter Gold" (oranga) as well as its big margarine factory which owned one of the largest whaling navy in the early 20th century.<ref>[http://www.hilter.de/de/Tourismus_und_Freizeit/geschichte History of Hilter (German)]</ref>
